{"id":"112349936201913060","created_at":"2024-04-28T17:06:17.693Z","in_reply_to_id":null,"in_reply_to_account_id":null,"sensitive":false,"spoiler_text":"","visibility":"public","language":"en","uri":"https://chaos.social/users/foosel/statuses/112349936201913060","url":"https://chaos.social/@foosel/112349936201913060","replies_count":6,"reblogs_count":7,"favourites_count":39,"quotes_count":0,"edited_at":null,"content":"\u003cp\u003eInspired by \u003cspan class=\"h-card\" translate=\"no\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://mastodon.art/@stiftnuersel\" class=\"u-url mention\"\u003e@\u003cspan\u003estiftnuersel\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e I decided to finally try to add book binding to my skill set and started with binding both books of 2D6 Dungeon (also a tip by \u003cspan class=\"h-card\" translate=\"no\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://mastodon.art/@stiftnuersel\" class=\"u-url mention\"\u003e@\u003cspan\u003estiftnuersel\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e).\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eEspecially sewing the paper stacks was incredibly relaxing. I put an audio book on (going through The Stormlight Archive again) and just went for it. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eDecided to go with a soft cover. The cardboard came from some deliveries and the fabric from the left overs of an old sewing project. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eQuite happy with the result 😊\u003c/p\u003e","reblog":null,"application":{"name":"Tusky","website":"https://tusky.app"},"account":{"id":"235099","username":"foosel","acct":"foosel","display_name":"Gina Häußge","locked":false,"bot":false,"discoverable":true,"indexable":true,"group":false,"created_at":"2020-01-01T00:00:00.000Z","note":"\u003cp\u003e🐒 Passionate code monkey 👩‍💻 Geek 🎮 Gamer 🧗‍♀️ Bouldering apprentice 💡 Problem solver 🐍 Python wrangler 🐙 Creator \u0026amp; Maintainer of OctoPrint\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eAdmin of plushies.social \u0026amp; one half of \u003cspan class=\"h-card\" translate=\"no\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https